    "created_at": "2016-07-21T14:22:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-21T14:22:10Z",
    "body": "In Mac, if an app is in full screen, the 'hide' function is disabled by default (take Finder for example). 'hide' is available ONLY after the app exits full screen. To me, client code should honour this behaviour by not calling \"hide()\" when the app is in full screen.\n"
  },
