    "created_at": "2016-08-24T10:42:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-24T10:42:11Z",
    "body": "@wenkaili , One way to work around this is to listen for the `leave-full-screen` event once before calling `setFullScreen(false);` and when that event is triggered then hiding the Window. See example code\n\n``` javascript\nwindow.on('close', function (e) {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    if(window.isFullScreen()){\n        window.once('leave-full-screen', function () {\n            window.hide();\n        })\n        window.setFullScreen(false);\n    }\n    else{\n        window.hide();\n    }\n});\n\n```\n"
